---
// biome-ignore lint/correctness/noUnusedImports: used in Astro template
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Install clip and generate your first CLI from a YAML schema in under 5 minutes."
>
  <div class="docs-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Get up and running with clip in under 5 minutes. You'll go from a YAML
      schema to a working CLI tool.
    </p>

    <h2 id="install">1. Install clip</h2>
    <p>Install the clip CLI globally using Bun:</p>
    <pre><code>bun install -g @clip/cli</code></pre>
    <p>Verify the installation:</p>
    <pre><code>clip --version</code></pre>

    <h2 id="create-schema">2. Create a schema</h2>
    <p>
      Create a <code>clip.yaml</code> file in your project directory. This file describes
      your API — its base URL, authentication, and endpoints.
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`name: "Todo API"
alias: todo
version: "1.0.0"
baseUrl: "http://localhost:3000"
auth:
  type: header
  headerName: "X-API-Key"
endpoints:
  - name: list
    method: GET
    path: /todos
    description: "List all todos"
    response:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        properties:
          id: string
          title: string
          completed: boolean

  - name: create
    method: POST
    path: /todos
    description: "Create a new todo"
    params:
      body:
        title:
          type: string
          required: true
    response:
      type: object
      properties:
        id: string
        title: string
        completed: boolean`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      See the <a href="/docs/schema/">Schema Reference</a> for the complete list
      of fields and options.
    </p>

    <h2 id="generate">3. Generate your CLI</h2>
    <p>
      Run <code>clip generate</code> to parse your schema and generate a
      complete TypeScript CLI project:
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip generate
✓ Parsed clip.yaml (2 endpoints)
✓ Generated CLI "todo" in .clip-output/todo/`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      The generated project lives in <code>.clip-output/todo/</code> and
      includes a fully working CLI with argument parsing, HTTP client, and type
      validation.
    </p>

    <h2 id="auth">4. Set up auth</h2>
    <p>Store your API credentials securely:</p>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip auth set todo --key "your-api-key"
✓ Credentials saved for "todo"`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Credentials are stored in <code>~/.clip/todo/credentials.json</code> with
      restricted file permissions (<code>0600</code>). The key value is never
      logged.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you omit <code>--key</code>, clip will prompt you interactively with
      hidden input.
    </p>

    <h2 id="install-cli">5. Install globally</h2>
    <p>Make your generated CLI available as a global command:</p>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip install
✓ Parsed clip.yaml (2 endpoints)
✓ Generated CLI "todo" in .clip-output/todo/
✓ Installed "todo" command globally`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Now you can run <code>todo</code> from anywhere in your terminal.
    </p>

    <h2 id="use">6. Use your CLI</h2>
    <p>Run commands just like any other CLI tool:</p>
    <pre><code>{`$ todo list
[{"id": "1", "title": "Buy milk", "completed": false}]

$ todo create --title "Write docs"
{"id": "2", "title": "Write docs", "completed": false}`}</code></pre>

    <h2 id="test">7. Run tests</h2>
    <p>
      clip auto-generates tests for each endpoint. Run them to verify your API
      responds correctly:
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip test todo
✓ GET /todos — 200, shape valid
✓ POST /todos — 201, shape valid
2/2 tests passed`}</code></pre>

    <h2 id="next-steps">Next steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="/docs/schema/">Schema Reference</a> — full documentation for <code
          >clip.yaml</code
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/docs/cli/">CLI Reference</a> — all clip commands and options
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .docs-prose {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .docs-prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .docs-prose h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .docs-prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose pre {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .docs-prose li a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
